 genetic research has revealed that ancient European populations were dark skinned for far longer than had originally been thought .
Rather than lightening as early humans migrated north from Africa around 40,000 years ago due to lower levels of sunlight , these first Homo sapiens retained their dark skin colour .
Genetic analysis has shown hunter gatherers living in Spain up to 8,500 years had dark skin .
DNA analysis shows that populations in Europe had to lighten .